ent State of Samoa) |6 November 1975 |- |[[Comoros|Union of the Comoros]]<ref name="Mfacdt"/> |13 November 1975 |- |[[Cape Verde|Republic of Cape Verde]]<ref name="Mfacdt"/> |25 April 1976 |- |[[Suriname|Republic of Suriname]] |28 May 1976 |- |[[Seychelles|Republic of Seychelles]]<ref name="Mfacdt"/> |30 June 1976 |- |[[Papua New Guinea|Independent State of Papua New Guinea]] |12 October 1976 |- |[[Liberia|Republic of Liberia]] <ref>Diplomatic relations were restored on 10 August 1993. Liberia resumed diplomatic ties with the ROC on 9 October 1989. Diplomatic relations with the PRC has been severed since 9 September 1997 because the Liberian Government's recognition of a "[[Two China]]s" Policy. However, the PRC and Liberia normalized their relations on 11 October 2003.</ref> |17 February 1977 |- |[[Jordan|Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan]] |7 April 1977 |- |[[Barbados]] |30 May 1977 |- |[[Oman|Sultanate of Oman]] |25 May 1978 |- |[[History of Libya under Muammar Gaddafi#Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya (1977–2011)|Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya]] (now [[Libya]]) |9 August 1978 |- |[[United States|United States of America]] |1 January 1979 |- |[[Djibouti|Republic of Djibouti]]<ref name="Mfacdt"/> |8 January 1979 |- |[[Portugal|Portuguese Republic]] |8 February 1979 |- |[[Ireland (state)|Ireland]] |22 June 1979 |}
